  "body": "<html><body><div class=\"field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item\" property=\"schema:text\"><p><br/><span>While the pandemic has certainly impacted mental health, available evidence to date suggests that suicide rates globally have not increased. RGA examines the evidence, cautions that the pandemic’s long-term effects on suicide are still evolving, and suggests the insurance industry has a significant role to play in suicide awareness and prevention moving forward. Read more </span><a href=\"https://www.internationalinsurance.org/sites/default/files/2022-09/COVID-19%20Pandemics%20Impact%20on%20Suicide%20Rates%20and%20Risk%20Factors%20-%20RGA%20Sept%202022.pdf\"><span><strong>here </strong></span></a><span>and register </span><a href=\"https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__event.on24.com_eventRegistration_EventLobbyServletV2-3Ftarget-3Dlobby20V2.jsp-26eventid-3D3932096-26sessionid-3D1-26format-3Dfhvideo1-26key-3D09BB7B5BE0C5CEFC68AC292E35403FF4-26eventuserid-3D557585644&amp;d=DwMGaQ&amp;c=euGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jXrwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&amp;r=7ZXFDtY4JHONZ-0ru0LrlWt_2_SKj9C6tzCwuEh2e_mf-wYEkB1_Ihs2imrnDMLb&amp;m=xopFg6ZYlgMCJF9h8cJKnxDU8GGGxzu-XNUObTvexLI&amp;s=ePmOVl2EGs_dvAMbSG_m5xb-DnE7qghFhLVeX0iG8RI&amp;e=\"><span><strong>here</strong></span></a><span> for the ‘Global Perspectives on Suicide: Data, Risk &amp; Prevention’ webinar, on September 27.</span></p></div></body></html>",
